<img src="http://www.champions-eternal.net/begging.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualagarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alagarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/24/01 8:10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/35/1088535.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> I have grouped with many warriors and there are times when even not taunting I can out taunt them just with my procs, sometimes I'll be with a warrior that gets beat down pretty fast and maybe you will want to taunt and get aggro to spread the damage around, also, as a paladin I don't have to tank like a warrior, I can prevent a mob from hitting me at all if it is stunnable, simply by stunning it with 2 or 3 stuns. But generally speaking it is preferred that a warrior does the tanking, if you are a 60 paladin, any decent 57+ warrior should be main tank. If you are in a group with a 56 or under warrior as a 60 paladin I think you should tank the mobs.<br>
