<br>
tell me 1 reason why you'd use a war over me?<br>
only time it would make sense is unstunnables or stuff needing defensive or anything hitting over 450ish. i am mt in hot lately cause no warriors have been on. heck i was chosen over a 57 warrior to be mt.<br>
<br>
sorry if i sound like i have a big head, but i'm damn proud to be a paladin and i'm tired of hearing how bad we are or others are better.<br>
<br>
paladins own you! that is all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utholumar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tholumar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/25/01 1:12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I like tanking also. I don't really have the wisdom gear to be a 2ndary healer all the time. I can do the job when I need to, but sometimes the 3 seconds spent casting Gheal could be better spent with a stun and a few taunts to get the mob off of the person. When I let a warrior tank in a group with a cleric I feel kinda of useless. If I stun the mob will agro on me, and then I'm not letting the warrior tank. And I get really bored just standing there with auto attack on. Healing the tank can help in bad situations or downtime.... but with a CH on the way, my heal just seems like wasted mana. <br>
<br>
When I do exp groups with a normal full group. (Very rare now adays.... I tend to partner with guildmates in small groups of two or three where we all know what the others can do and what they should do..) If I dont tank I feel like all i do is cast DG, push auto attack, and do some crowd control when we get adds..... I dunno about you guys... If I'm not stunning, I'm not doing one of my most  effective tatics....<br>
<br>
<br>
Tholumar Enlightener<br>
Level 55 Knight<br>
Seekers of Unity<br>
Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utherus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Therus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 1:59:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> I have no idea why any paladin would want to tank if a warrior of similar level is around. Warriors will always have at least 1k hp more than paladins, and that's a huge advantage in terms of tanking. Yes, you have 5k hp fully buffed, but I bet most lvl 60 warriors will have at least 6k hp fully buffed. <br>
<br>
IMHO, paladins are at their best when they take on the secondary tank role. All the things Octella described, such as root parking, healing, DS, etc are best done when paladins are not the main tank. How can a main tank tank adds, or root park adds? How can a main tank heal the group if there is a mob keep beating on him to interrupt his spells? If the main tank is also the puller, how can he spare time to DS the group if the group keep asking him to bring more mobs?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaladril1961.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadril1961</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 8:27:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> If you are fighting mobs that cast or want to stun to reduce the mobs damage output then you are going to be tanking anyway. Its going to be very difficult for the warrior to get that mob off you if you are chain stunning so you might just as well tank it. Allowing the warrior to tank equals not stunning. What you probably don't want is to have the warrior taunting away and you stunning like mad and have the mob constantly going back and forth between you, so if the warrior is tanking you will have to cut back on stunning or risk pissing off the cleric. <br>
<br>
If the warrior can hit the mob in the back I also think that's a benefit, they arent being parried/riposted/dodged from there and thus are doing more damage. I'd rather have the Paladin get parried than the warrior.<br>
<br>
Even though warrior armor has some better ac in general, there are alot of new armor pieces in Luclin that are going to allow paladins to stay up with them in ac (my ac is up a bunch already from luclin items since it came out) and I think his equal hp/ac situation will occur a little more often in the future. Throw a shield on a paladin and it should just about make up the ac difference. To me having a paladin tank makes a fair amount of sense. <p><b>
