<a href=mailto:sblue@bright.net>sblue@bright.net</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 10:20:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> The warrior will always take less damage if same lvl, and same ac. Their skill caps are higher thus less damage.<br>
<br>
Now if things(ac/hp) were nearly equal and the warrior is lower lvl then you then you should be tanking. Level is the most important stat in every combat calculation. The difference in tanking between a lvl 55 and a lvl 60  is rather large. Mabye not against low blues but against npcs 50-55 it will show. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 11:12:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> What the heck is a secondary tank anyway? Sounds like a fifh wheel to me. Either your taking the hits or your not.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiscandar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iscandar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 11:40:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> I (like many folks who posted already) think it's unlikely that a warrior and a Pally of the same level will have the same AC and HP.  BUT, if they do happen to, then my take on that is this:<br>
<br>
The warrior should tank.  That's what he does, that's all he really can do.  Let him do what he does best.  If for some reason heals are needed (you get adds and the adds are beating on the chanter and/or cleric) from you... you can't heal those folks if you're the one tanking the "kill" mob.  Just my 2 cents ;) <p><img SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~magiq77/smallsig.jpg" height=246 width=300></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulocrovik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Locrovik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 8:10:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tanking</span><hr size=1> A secondary tank Cylria??  That is the person who helps keep mobs busy when you dont have a chanter.  Or did you forget that not everygroup has to have an enchanter to be sucessful?  <br>
<br>
And for those of you who think that this is an unlikely situation.  WAKE UP!!  It is not an actual in game experience.  I was just wondering who would get healed less.  The question was answered a quite a ways back, by someone who actually read what he was posting under <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I know that a paladin should have less HP AC as a warrior of the same level, but that wasnt my question.  I know a warrior can probably hold aggro better than a paladin, BUT yet again that was not my question.  I will try to draw it out in crayon so you all can read it this time not just a few.<br>
<br>
Paladin 1- LVL60<br>
              5000HP<br>
              1400AC<br>
              1100ATK<br>
<br>
Warrior 1- LVL 60<br>
              5000HP<br>
              1400AC<br>
              1100ATK<br>
<br>
WHO IS GOING TO REQUIRE MORE COMPLETE HEALS? PALADIN OR WARRIOR???<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry for those of you that read this and actually took the time to read the question the first time.  <br>
<br>
  Thank you <br>
       Loc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ureplay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>replay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 8:17:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> A Paladin would require more heals simply because of his lower defensive skill caps of Dodge, Parry and Riposte.  The situation you present is ideal though. It's basically a Paladin with better gear over a Warrior or a Warrior with junk gear. This also doesn't consider if the Warrior uses some of his disciplines such as Defensive.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphantomsix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phantomsix</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.eqdestiny.com/images/p6/p6icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 8:53:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> let the warrior tank.  He does it better and you cant reliably cast any spells while tanking.  If you have aggro and someone in the group needs a quick battle heal, the warrior cant do anything about it. <p>Phantomsix Solarblade<BR>
Destiny<BR>
Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/26/01 10:22:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Secondary what?</span><hr size=1> When I'm playing my wizzy or my paladin (my other two are an enchanter and bard so they have better tactics) and some adds agro on one of the other casters, I just root them so the casters can back away from it, then go back to killing the primary target. No one needs to tank them, no one should waste time fighting lots of different mobs when you should focus on killing one quickly. No one needs to waste HPs being a secondary tank.<br>
<br>
As to your question, its been answered, who ever has the better defensive skills might require less healing, usually this will be the warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=13570.topic&start=21&stop=24>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13506.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13541.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13570.topic&index=20><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=13570.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=13570.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13570.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13570.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select n